<br>
I have a better example for you then the government example, because face it, if we use the government as an example everyone will be able to come up with some obscure instance... Lets take a house... I buy a house. Of course, I cannot afford the 150,000 dollars so I get the bank to get me a loan. (This should work with Drac's skewed we are &quot;leasing&quot; our EQ time example...) During my time of &quot;owning&quot; the house, I make changes to it. I invest time into improving it or... trashing it with drunken parties. heh. Now when I want to move to another house... I still do not &quot;own&quot; my house. Yet, if I can find some sucker to buy it, then I can make a profit or take a loss. It is totally up to me what I charge for the house. If I charge 500,000 dollars and someone *does* buy it, then good for me. I can then pay off my loan and obtain another loan for another house.<br>
<br>
Does the bank restrict me on how much I can sell for? No. All that restricts me is what someone will pay for it. If I put a lot of time into improvements ( Like made my garage into a level 50 garage hehe) Then I can probably sell for more then I paid. If I wasted my time being a drunk (most likely) then I will be lucky to break even.<br>
<br>
I agree Verant &quot;owns&quot; the bytes of data... but they do not &quot;own&quot; the time anyone puts into their characters. If you truly believe they do &quot;own&quot; that time, and can look me in the eye and tell me you would not be mad if they deleted you for no reason tomorrow (and all of your uber gear) then I will pay more attention to your one-sided banter...<br>
