<br>
They say that in order to get certain items you need to be a full-time gamer. However, if they are allowed to &quot;aquire&quot; these items for us and resell them, do you think normal gamers will be able to get them? No, of course not.  Think about it.  That item will be camped/monopolized by companies like BSI who send people to get those items in the same time we could be using to get them ourselves.  Those companies  &quot;steal&quot; the time we payed to play the game/camp the item only to sell them back to us b/c we couldn't get that item b/c they were camping it....who has the monopoly now?  Basically the only way to get certain items would be to buy it from them, or get extremely lucky, and catch that camp at a time when they weren't holding it (good luck).<br>
<br>
If this ever happened in Everquest, I would start looking for other ways to spend my time.  If i pay to play a game, I would like to be able to aquire an item myself instead of having to pay even more to get it.  Sure, its nice to have the option to buy it online, but to legaliz it, and turn it into a profitable buisness will end up stealing from the people who play in the end.<br>
