<br>
I totally understand the appeal to many players.  But to those who wish not to pay more money, and are willing to spend the time, its kind of unfair.  The point of alot of these items is that they are also status symbols.   Having them shows what you went through to get them or buy them with game currency.  To make it so everyone potentially has access, would cheapen the gameplay.  Thats just my opinion.<br>
<br>
In another thought, I would think that being in that line of buisness would be very unstable.  What if verant all of a sudden made an item no-drop at whim (they tend to do this kind of thing).  Man, that would suck if you were workin for a farming CO that had alot of income from that item.  Then, as they say.. easy come easy go.<br>
<br>
For me, the bottom line is this - <br>
Whatever happens, as long as they can balance it so that if I choose to camp an item I won't have to compete with a professional farmer, I would have no problem.  Until then, I remain skeptical of the overall advantage to having this system in place.<br>
